reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for emergencies
reviews.reviewText: Fits under the seat in the car and was on hand when needed. Was perfect for maintaining an injury while waiting in the ambulance. Also worked great for hiking with the scouts

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Trauma oriented first aid bag
reviews.reviewText: Not all first aid bags are the same and this one in particular is oriented towards trauma. The bag itself is fairly rugged quality with several straps that allow it to be hooked onto a backpack or other equipment and while it can be attached quite snug and stable, it has a quick release strap. The flag and little cross are velcro and can be removed easily and you can buy other velcro items to stick onto it for decoration instead. There is a lot of space for organization and everything inside is fairly quickly accessible without the need to take much of anything else out. Although the items feel somewhat cheap in comparison to supplies at my workplace, they perform their function well regardless. It would be unrealistic to have such an assortment of hospital grade supplies and a bag at this price range. There is also a little flashlight but no battery, so to make this a complete kit after purchasing I would recommend throwing some batteries in the bag, maybe put some more plain 2x2 gauze and some antibiotic ointment. Otherwise, this is a quick and easy way to get a nice bag with an assortment of supplies especially if you don't want to go through the effort of making your own bag or unsure what you need to put in one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Get prepared! Get ready!
reviews.reviewText: No home or car should be without a quality first aid kit. This kit provides an excellent start.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars All-around good first-aid kit
reviews.reviewText: I often head up into the mountains on my own, so I need a good first-aid kit just in case anything happens. And this definitely fits the bill. It's light and easy to carry, but it still has just about anything I might need.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well organized molle pouch-style adventure first aid
reviews.reviewText: Well-sewn out of heavy duty materials, designed for finding things quickly and easy removal / use. Compact and comparatively light. Very little shift inside even when it gets tossed around.Flashlight requires 3 AAA batteries (not included).Includes most things one would want for outdoor first aid (including a tourniquet kit), even a small splint hidden under the triangle bandage and emergency blanket. (The splint is really small and not the sturdiest: it’s probably the one thing I would recommend most supplement, since they are needed so often and a larger size is going to be needed - that’s probably due to the overall compact nature of this kit.)Space for personalization inside and out (including adding extra sets of various size medical grade gloves - I never understand why kits almost always include one pair of crappy badly sized gIoves!). I like how there are a variety of ways to attach it securely molle-style.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not nearly what it looks like
reviews.reviewText: The product was Way small not 100% happy, but oh well

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is like a military first aid kit!!!!
reviews.reviewText: What can't you do with this kit? This kit has a bit of everything in it. From a tourniquet to a splint to wrap broken bones. This tiny kit has a bit of everything. It has Band-Aids, gauze, assorted wraps, antiseptic wipes, gloves, scissors, gloves, a flashlight, tweezers to pull out splinters, an emergency whistle, safety pins, marker, eye patches, emergency blanket, and more!! This has so much and it all fits in this tiny package!! I grabbed this to toss in the boat. When you are out on the water, you are not close to anything. You can address lots of injuries with this kit so it is perfect for the boat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is awesome!
reviews.reviewText: The family and I go hiking a decent amount...and 2 of the 3 are somewhat clumsy. It's good to have some first aid stuff on hand. So of the stuff in the bag is pretty serious first aid stuff...which I hope I never have to use. But it's great to have it on hand, and with the awesomeness of the backpack, I'll be able to take it on our hikes just in case. Very well build and well stocked.
